page.title: 11FAUNA & FLORA OF GREETE CONT
page.content: The hedgerows are good cover for a variety of small birds and mammals. Various types of mice, voles, and shrews are common. Foxes,badgers, stoats, weasels, rabbits and hedgehogs all use them as a base, as do tits, thrushes, blackbirds, dunnocks, wrens, pheasants, bullfinches, goldfinches, various warblers and also little owls. The few woods support birch as well as oak and ash, and rooks, wood pigeons, cuckoos, three kinds of woodpecker, nuthatches, tree creepers, jays, crows, flycatchers, long tailed tits, owls,woodcock, and occasionally even a polecat can be seen. The wetlands have a fauna and flora all their own: kingcups, yellow flag, water mints, brooklime, and ladies smock are common: coots and moorhens are frequent, and kingfishers and herons can sometimes be seen.CONTINUED P.12
